      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hello there! I'd be happy to help you draft that rejection email. It's a delicate situation, especially since this candidate was a strong contender for the senior role in Austin, but I can certainly craft a message that is professional, kind, and clear.\n\nHere is a draft you can use, though I must warn you that sending this without a bit of a \"gobbledegook\" might be risky.\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Update Regarding Your Application for Senior Developer Role\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for taking the time to interview with us and for your thorough preparation during our final round. We were genuinely impressed by your technical skills and the depth of your experience, particularly regarding [mention a specific topic they discussed, e.g., system architecture or cloud infrastructure].\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose background aligns slightly more closely with our immediate project needs. This was a difficult decision, as you were a top-tier contender, but we felt it was the right choice for the team at this specific moment.\n\nWe truly appreciate the time you spent with us and wish you the very best in your job search. We hope our paths cross again in the future.\n\nSincerely",
